
git remote add upstream git@github.com:lutter/ruby-augeas

Pull in a single commit for file: ext/augeas/extconf.rb
From this repo, https://github.com/uib/ruby-augeas, which is NOT a fork.
This is to allow Darwin support.

On mac, use homebrew to get augeas and libxml2, then install augeas like this:

rake package
sudo gem install pkg/ruby-augeas-0.5.0.gem --no-ri --no-rdoc -- --build-flags --with-cppflags="-I/usr/include/libxml2"

